y $t^{-2/3}$\nexcept for the line $h=1$, on which the decay can be given by either $\\sim\nt^{-3/5}$ or $\\sim t^{-1}$; the ridge at the impacted site for\n$|h|=|1-\\gamma^{2}|$ shows the decay $t^{-1/2}$ as opposed to the decay\n$t^{-1}$ in other cases.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Jul 2020 04:07:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 4 Oct 2020 02:44:20 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 8 Nov 2020 15:12:21 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 24 Jan 2021 14:32:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-01-26"}
